<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="449" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,671,1457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Brownish yellow; forewing with small dark brown spot near middle of subcostal region, on apex of clavus and in apical cells; ocelli reddish (
<figureCitation box="[442,617,776,799]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2A–C, E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,671,1457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Crown produced parabolically with anterior margin angularly rounded to front and with some longitudinal striations on vertex and three carinae and two sutures medially (
<figureCitation box="[746,860,845,868]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
); ocelli located 4.0 times their diameter distant from eyes (
<figureCitation box="[213,327,880,903]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2C</figureCitation>
); coronal suture extended to midlength of vertex, median length of vertex 1.5–2.0 times length next to eyes (
<figureCitation box="[212,355,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2B, C</figureCitation>
); fore femur row IC with 11 setae (
<figureCitation box="[730,843,914,937]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2O</figureCitation>
); apical setal formula of hind femur 2+2+1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,671,1457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Male genitalia. Style moderately long with apex beak-like and filamentously tapered to apex, tenuous distally (
<figureCitation box="[158,281,984,1007]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2M</figureCitation>
). Connective Y-shaped, stem very long, 2.0 times length of arms, single process posteriorly on ventral surface strongly bifurcated, scissorlike (
<figureCitation box="[584,691,1018,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2J</figureCitation>
), directed ventrally and curved dorsad more strongly (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1423,1018,1041]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2J, L</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with dorsal atrium developed elongate and with one denticulate process on each side in caudal view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2G, K</figureCitation>
); with basal paired sinuate processes closer to shaft and directly articulating to connective (
<figureCitation box="[1203,1307,1088,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
Figure 
<date box="[1282,1307,1088,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">2I</date>
</figureCitation>
); shaft with slight basal dorsal bulge, curved dorsad and tapered to apex with long pair of basal processes, processes subapically expanded, tapered distally (
<figureCitation box="[443,581,1157,1180]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,244,1677,1699]" captionTargetBox="[236,1342,201,1635]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[226,1360,191,1655]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Favintiga paragracilipenis sp. nov. A, E. Male dorsal and lateral view; B–C. head and thorax, dorsal view and dorsoanterior view; D.face; F–H.pygofer,lateral, caudal and ventral view; I–L.aedeagus and connective, caudal, ventral, dorsal and lateral view; M.style, dorsal view; N.valve and subgenital plates,ventral view; O.fore femur,anteriorview." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1146421/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Figure 2F, L</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
