<subSubSection box="[199,1433,1225,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,671,1457]" box="[199,1433,1225,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1226,1249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lu &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2018" box="[562,739,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paragracilipenis">
<emphasis box="[562,739,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">paragracilipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; indicates that this new species is very similar to 
<emphasis box="[1272,1433,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shang &amp; Zhang. A" authorityYear="2006" box="[1272,1429,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipenis">F. gracilipenis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="449" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,671,1457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1261,1284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is very similar to 
<emphasis box="[693,855,1260,1284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shang &amp; Zhang. A" authorityYear="2006" box="[693,851,1260,1284]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipenis">F. gracilipenis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
but differs in the following characters: 1) style apical apophysis filamentously tapered to apex (more slender than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shang &amp; Zhang. A" authorityYear="2006" box="[827,954,1295,1319]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipenis">
<emphasis box="[827,954,1295,1319]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">gracilipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 2) connective with stem longer than apical process (process equal to stem in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shang &amp; Zhang. A" authorityYear="2006" box="[531,658,1329,1353]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipenis">
<emphasis box="[531,658,1329,1353]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">gracilipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 3) process of connective directed ventrally and curved dorsad more strongly than the latter; 4) aedeagus with processes closer to aedeagal shaft on each side, subapically expanded, tapered to apex and slightly shorter than shaft in ventral and lateral view (more distant from shaft and nearly equal in length to shaft in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shang &amp; Zhang. A" authorityYear="2006" box="[236,363,1433,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipenis">
<emphasis box="[236,363,1433,1457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">gracilipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and 5) shaft with slight basal dorsal bulge (absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shang &amp; Zhang. A" authorityYear="2006" box="[949,1076,1433,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Favintiga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilipenis">
<emphasis box="[949,1076,1433,1457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="449">gracilipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
